<div class="level-title">Level 677{{Underline|FFeedd}}“Expanse of Electricity”
</div>
{{Underline|FFeedd}}
<Div style="background: var(--theme-page-background-color--secondary);margin: 0 1em;padding: 15px;border-radius: 25px; backdrop-filter: contrast(120%) brightness(0.3);">
{{Class Custom Image|hexagon=⌁|color-h=30|text-color=lightorange|class=2|safety=Unsafe|security=Stable|entity=Minimal Entity Count|bg-image=Level677-newimage.png}}

== Description ==
{{Blurimage|file=Level677-newimage.png|align=Right|caption=First ever image of this level. Photographer is unknown.}}
[[Level 677]], known as the '''''“Expanse of Electricity,”''''' is an endless expanse of cracking concrete dominated by a persistent dark orange fog. The ground is uneven in places, which forms shallow puddles that naturally gather stagnant water, debris, and corroded metallic fragments. The exact source of the orange hue within the mist is still unknown, although it consistently intensifies during rainfall and significantly reduces visibility.

The most definable features of this level are the numerous electricity transmission towers. Each tower is heavily rusted and appears structurally weakened, but still manages to stand upright. These towers are connected by a sparse network of wires, many of which are broken, loose, or terminate abruptly. Despite their design, no electrical activity has ever been detected within the towers or wiring. Their arrangement across the concrete landscape shows no obvious pattern or functional purpose.<ref>Unusually, an arrangement pattern can rarely be found within some areas of the level, as shown in the first image.</ref>

The environment is cold and wet, with temperatures sometimes being just above freezing. Light precipitation occurs frequently, and manifests as soft droplets. At irregular cases, this transitions into periods of heavy rain, which causes the fog intensity to increase into a dense orange haze that can limit visibility to a few meters. Aside from subtle wind blows, creaking of the rusty structures and rainfall, the level is strangely silent.

Many objects are distributed randomly throughout the expanse, which include rusty tools, damaged mechanical components, and industrial equipments. Although a few number of these items may still hold limited practical value, most are too aged to be useful. Their origin is unknown, and no obvious signs of prior habitation or organized activity have been identified.
</Div>
{{Underline|FFeedd}}
<Div style="background: var(--theme-page-background-color--secondary);margin: 0 1em;padding: 15px;border-radius: 25px; backdrop-filter: blur(5px) contrast(120%) brightness(0.3);">
== Entities ==
=== Corrosion Claws ===
'''Corrosion Claws''' are small, and spider-like entities that inhabit the bases and mid-sections of the level’s electricity towers. Their bodies are covered in a matte and rusty-colored upper shell, and each limb has a sharp claw, which is useful for scraping and weakening metallic surfaces. These entities feed by digging their claws into tower frameworks and extracting trace minerals, which leaves behind lines and patches that resemble natural corrosion.

They are mostly non-aggressive toward humans unless provoked, although usually try to scatter quickly across metal surfaces with fast movements instead of attacking back. Their presence is indicated by subtle tapping sounds and brief flashes of movement within the electrical tower.

=== Fog Glider ===
{{Blurimage|caption=An image of two '''Fog Gliders''' on an electrical tower. The image was taken after the entity's existence was confirmed.|align=left|file=Fog glider.png}}
'''Fog Gliders''' are large, and bird-like predatory entities that glide silently through the orange mist above [[Level 677]]. Their appearance is loosely similar to an eagle, although their bodies are longer, and their beaks are longer and more sharp than the beaks of any known bird species. Their feathers feature a soft orange sheen that can blend in well with the surrounding fog, which provides effective natural camouflage.

'''Fog Gliders''' are opportunistic hunters, and usually circle high above the towers before executing sudden diving toward movement on the concrete below. Their calls are extremely hard to hear, and are described by witnesses as metallic whistles far away.

=== Corrosion Eater ===
'''Corrosion Eaters''' are squat, and crab-like entities that linger on the lower expanse, most usually near puddles or decaying metal debris. Unlike [[The Frontrooms|Frontrooms]] crabs, they have only two thick legs, two big claws, and their head protrudes from the body via a short but muscular neck.

These entities emit a strong odor that mimic humid, and oxidized steel; which is a pheromonal lure that attracts '''Corrosion Claws''', which they prey upon. Despite their strange gait, '''Corrosion Eaters''' can do sudden bursts of speed when attacking, and use their strong claws to crack open '''Corrosion Claws'''’ shells. They show some interest in humans unless provoked, although reports note that the metallic odor they produce becomes stronger when agitated as a defense mechanism.
</div>
